[select the **show more** control to display additional info]
The Uyghur language, formerly known as Eastern Turki, is a Turkic language with 8 to 11 million speakers, spoken primarily by the Uyghur people in the Xinjiang Uyghur Autonomous Region of Western China. Significant communities of Uyghur-speakers are located in Kazakhstan and Uzbekistan. Uyghur is an official language of the Xinjiang Uyghur Autonomous Region.

The term \"East Turkestan\" is inextricably linked with politics. In general, most of the toponyms for places in Central Asia do not reflect the region\'s diversity. The history of Xinjiang in particular is contested between the government of China and Uyghur separatists, as is which name to use \"Xinjiang\" or \"Uyghur Autonomous Region\" or \"East Turkestan\" or \"Shinjang\"(derived from the Uyghur pronunciation of Xinjiang). In modern separatist usage. \"Uyghurstan\", which means \"land of the Uyghurs\", is a synonym for Xinjiang or a potential state in Xinjiang. However there is no consensus among separatists about whether to use \"East Turkestan\" or \"Uyghurstan\"....
