At least 31 people have been killed by blasts at a market in China\'s western region of Xinjiang.

Authorities say the explosions took place when two vehicles rammed into a crowd at an open air market in the city of Urumqi.

An incendiary device is said to have been thrown from one car while the other exploded.

China has blamed a string of violent attacks in recent months on militant separatists from Muslim ethnic Uighurs. 
